{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775898811298,"sessionID":"ses_2842ef4e0ffeoBcV4suEXEi79D","part":{"id":"prt_d7bd14a77001EgvnTmwBXBZ1rz","messageID":"msg_d7bd13047001X9WvCu28WyfMqs","sessionID":"ses_2842ef4e0ffeoBcV4suEXEi79D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/notes.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/notes.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型 — Notes\n2: \n3: ## Status\n4: Initialized: 2026-04-11\n5: \n6: ## Open Questions\n7: - Should metadata support attachments/binary data?\n8: - How to handle metadata schema migrations?\n9: - Should we implement a caching layer for frequently accessed metadata?\n10: - What is the maximum metadata size limit?\n11: - Should we support metadata encryption for sensitive fields?\n12: \n13: ## References\n14: - See AR-024 for service implementation patterns\n15: - Related to agent configuration management\n16: - Check existing storage implementations for interface alignment\n17: \n18: ## Change Log\n19: - 2026-04-11: Initial scaffold created\n\n(End of file - total 19 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型 — Notes\n\n## Status\nInitialized: 2026-04-11\n\n## Open Questions\n- Should metadata support attachments/binary data?\n- How to handle metadata schema migrations?\n- Should we implement a caching layer for frequently accessed metadata?\n- What is the maximum metadata size limit?\n- Should we support metadata encryption for sensitive fields?\n\n## References\n- See AR-024 for service implementation patterns\n- Related to agent configuration management\n- Check existing storage implementations for interface alignment\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026-04-11: Initial scaffold created","trun